 REAT.

I have a huge amount in a foreign account opened by a customer of mine, he died in a freakplane crash, and all my efforts to trace his next of kin was for to
declare him out of the family. However, there were some relatives (myself included) who were
confined in South Africa and this was where the problems started.

I have contacted you in view of the fact that the South Africa legislation does not recognize the death of a foreigner as
natural coming of age, and therefore such case would not qualify for financial support of any form.

The South Africa legal codes on this point has made it illegal to support a person as a "son of a South African" and thus
the fund must inure to the family members or next of kin in question. The South African government has
criminalized providing foreign assistance to anyone that provides a next of kin to any dead person, and this
has made finding the family member difficult.

The South African parliament recently passed a new criminalized assistance in respect to human trafficking which
is very concerning.



It is therefore upon this discovery that I decided to donate this fund to any charity organization that will utilize this funds in a
wise way. I want to assure you that this transaction is 100% risk free and that you should not feel any urgency in your appeal.I am aware that this
transaction could come to you as a surprise as you do not know me personally, I want you to have a look at this site http://relay.zoom.com I am relaying via this medium that you will be the origin of this fund.

I want this fund to be managed properly and it is because of this, that I will be needing a trusted international partner who will assist me in transferring this funds to your account.You will be entitled to 30% of the total fund while 10% will be set aside for any incidental expenses that may happen during
